# Trivy ignore file. Suppress specific vulnerability IDs that are assessed as
# not applicable or knowingly accepted — one ID per line, each with a comment
# explaining why. Keep this empty unless a finding needs a documented, deliberate
# exception; a bare suppression with no rationale is worse than no suppression.
#
# Example:
#   CVE-2024-00000  # not reachable: (dep) <reason>; revisit when a fix is released

CVE-2026-39822       # not reachable: (supercronic) reads a trusted crontab and execs, no os.Root on untrusted paths; on latest upstream. Revisit when a build against Go >= 1.26.5 ships.
GHSA-hrxh-6v49-42gf  # not reachable: (rclone) runs as a CLI copy client, never a gRPC/xDS server; on latest upstream. Revisit when a build against grpc >= 1.82.1 ships.
